Etherframe
==========

License:
--------
Released under new BSD license.

Synopsis:
---------
Etherframe is a simple ethernet frame receiver with bare up-level protocol decoding and cable statistics.

The intended use is to measure EMI, noise, and signal attenuation in ethernet cables placed in an environment disturbed by strong magnetic fields, but can also be used as a normal network sniffer.
Typically the used cables are Cat.3-4-5 or higher Cat.:

Platforms:
----------
Etherframe currently compile and run on Debian.

The listeth program displays a list of network interface names.
Usage:
------
./listeth

You need to be logged in as root to run the program.
Usage:
------
./etherframe [<interface name>] [<promiscuous mode>]

Where <interface name> is a name from the listeth listing, and <promiscuous mode> is 0=disables, 1=enabled.
